race.comment: SUPER NUI (7) warmed up late on resumption with an eye catching fourth over 1100m at Warwick Farm when shouldering the 60.5kg. Regular rider sticks and she gets out to her preferred trip with a tidy second-up record. Hard to stop. OAKFIELD JUPITER (6) covered ground early from the awkward gate on resumption when a dominant winner over 1200m at Randwick in this class. Reunited with Aaron Bullock who had the two wins on her in the first campaign. Up in weight and can continue to raise the bar. MOTOSCAFO (5) tough mare who indicated she has come back in good order when taking good ground off OAKFIELD JUPITER to run second over 1200m at Randwick. Gets a better set-up and no shock to see her go one better. ALABAMA STATE (19) kept fresh and will appreciate the drop in weight. Will go back from the gate and be ridden for luck. Minor place chance. PUERTO BANUS (3) showed good improvement at Scone over the 1100m and can give plenty of cheek.
